               <head>Sufi commentary, A'inah-yi haqa'iq numa</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Āʾīnah-'i ḥaqāʾiq'numā</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89003718 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008107714" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_955-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8247">Āʾīnah-'i ḥaqāʾiq'numā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8247">آئينۀ حقايق نما</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rare unidentified Sūfī commentary on the metaphysical and cosmological work <title>Jām-i Jahān'numā</title> attributed here to <persName key="person_12221201" role="att">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad [ibn] ʿIzz al-Dīn "Maghribī", also known as Muḥammad Shīrīn (d. 809/1406)</persName>, by an unnamed author 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work, transcribed in fine scholarly nastaʿlīq, contains several diagrams, of which one example (ff. 62v-63r) is particularly detailed </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 86r): 5 Muḥarram 1035/7 October 1625 </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning; torn, wormholes; net overlay; rebound </p>
                        <p>Octagonal seal impressions and inscriptions (ff. 1v, 86v): mālikuhu khātimuh (seal:) <persName key="person_f7507" role="asn">Rukn al-Dīn al-Ḥusaynī</persName> [<persName key="person_48143049" role="oth">Emperor Farrukhsiyar</persName> regnal year] 3, 1127/1715 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
